      [
        {
          "id": 1621279199080,
          "type": "text",
          "content": "\"<h2>Mangroves</h2><p><strong>Australia possesses about 7% of the world's mapped mangroves. Between 1996 and 2016, the region lost roughly 3% of its mangrove area </strong>(a net loss of 270 km²). This net change included both 342 km² of loss and 71 km² of gain.</p><p><br></p><p>As of 2016, the region had 9,470 km² of mangrove forest.</p>\""
        }
      ],
